    <h1>Chocolate Fudge</h1>
    
    <img src="chocolate-fudge.jpg" alt="A rich, decadent slice of chocolate fudge">
    
    <h2>Description</h2>
    <p>
      Chocolate fudge is a classic confection that combines rich cocoa with smooth, creamy texture. 
      This indulgent treat is perfect for any occasion and can be made right in your own kitchen. 
      With just a few simple ingredients and basic cooking techniques, you'll be able to create 
      professional-quality fudge that rivals anything from a specialty candy shop.
    </p>
    <p>
      The key to perfect chocolate fudge is careful temperature control and proper beating techniques. 
      Follow these simple steps and you'll have delicious homemade fudge ready to share with friends 
      and family. Store it in an airtight container and it will stay fresh for weeks!
    </p>
    
    <h2>Ingredients</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>2 cups granulated sugar</li>
      <li>3/4 cup unsweetened cocoa powder</li>
      <li>1 cup milk</li>
      <li>1/2 cup butter</li>
      <li>1 teaspoon vanilla extract</li>
      <li>Pinch of salt</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h2>Steps</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>Combine sugar, cocoa powder, milk, and butter in a heavy saucepan. Heat over medium heat, stirring constantly until the mixture reaches 238°F (soft ball stage) on a candy thermometer.</li>
      <li>Remove from heat and let cool for 5 minutes without stirring. Add vanilla extract and salt, then beat with an electric mixer or wooden spoon until the mixture becomes thick and loses its glossy appearance. Pour into a buttered 8x8 inch pan and allow to cool completely before cutting into squares.</li>
    </ol>
    
